Public transport (MHD) pragois will introduce, Wednesday, the chip into their ticketing system
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be recorded in the history of Pražský Dopravní podnik (the Pragoise Agency of Transport) as the date on which they will ride in the subway, trams and buses the first passengers, who, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, it is accessible for about one hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard smart card.
Passengers can buy a coupon 30 days or 90 days (this coupon will be valid from 1 January 2009) and both register it on their smart card at the information points and offices of the Dopravní podnik (the Transportation Agency), located in the metro stations Muzeum, Městek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday, there is also the possibility to buy coupons over the Internet on the Dopravní podnik web pages: www.dpp.cz.
More than four hundred people took advantage of the service in the morning.
Those who will begin to use the online store can permanently forget the windows in the metro stations, where they have so far had to tramp impatience in long queues in order to obtain paper tickets.
Indeed, they will buy their coupon over the Internet and will be recorded on their Opencard card in one of the 13 Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"In these points of contact, there is at the disposal of passengers a window with trained staff, which will help those interested with Internet purchase and, in addition, will record the coupon they bought on their card," says project spokesman Martin Opatrný.
Along with libraries, it will also be possible to record the electronic coupons on the Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, recalling the machines to compose tickets and passengers may have already noticed them in the stations of Roztyly Metro, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be eighty," said Opatrný.
An automatic will control the coupon instead of the driver
The machines that will work from tomorrow, are easy to use.
Just insert the Opencard chip card and the coupon bought previously will register itself on the card.
