I think in photography the portrait is the most difficult kind.
You're standing in front of people, characters you don't know or who just give you a few minutes to get a picture of them.
Despite these circumstances, as a photographer, I always try to make my ideas come true."
This collection of portraits of the current flamenco called "Flamenco - people", is exhibited at the Galerie El Fotómata, located at the 20th Street of Mata (street parallel to the People's of Hercules) which will be opened until 16 October next.
